{
  "stem": "12462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Baldwin immediately said to me, look, we're got a lot of documents that are laying here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We want to get at them soon.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the first thing we have to do is straighten up the rooms, which most of the windows of the Palace of Justice had been blown in by bombing or shelling.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as a consequence, there was a tremendous amount of books on the floor and places-- there was one part of the building had received a direct bomb hit, but that didn't affect 9/10 of the building.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the windows were out, and we had to fly to Paris and get windows that the Belgians had made or that someone had kept underground and have them flown back in order to put windows in-- a lot of the windows of the Palace of Justice, which became the headquarters for the trials.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At first, we went to the Grand Hotel, which it was later mainly the place for VIPs that were passing through Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I didn't stay there more than about a week, and I was transferred out to Schlegelstrasse.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Bill Baldwin, Colonel Baldwin, had a-- a residence out there, and about four or five of us were made a part of that or lived there while we traveled back and forth each morning by Army car to the Nuremberg Courthouse.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a Lieutenant Reitzer, R-E-I-T-Z-E-R, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] another major whose name I forget, who didn't get along very well with other people there and soon left.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I can't remember his name, and I would just as soon not give it to you anyway.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
